ABUJA – The Office of the Head of Civil Service of the Federation(OHCSF) has trained over 1,200 officers in Mandatory Continuing Professional Development (MOPD) in the bid to enhance their on-the-job professionalism. The Permanent Secretary, Common Services Office, Office of the Head Civil Service of the Federation, Mr. Ibrahim Yusuf, disclosed this when he received the leadership of the Association of National Accountants of Nigeria (ANAN) led by its first Vice President, Dr. James Ekarere Neminebor, on a courtesy visit to his Office in Abuja. A statement on Wednesday by AbdulGaniyu Aminu, Director, Communications in the OHCSF, quoted Yusuf as saying that the Office of the Head of Service accords high priority to the training of staff to ensure effective service delivery and attainment of national development goals. OHCSF Decries Increasing Incidences of Sudden Deaths Among… FG Mulls Over 5-Year Pre-retirement Training For Civil Servants Representing the Head of the Civil Service of the Federation, the Permanent Secretary assured ANAN members that the Office would continue to support the annual ANAN conferences by ensuring members of staff who belong to the association attend their conferences. The President of ANAN, represented at the event by Dr. James Ekerare Neninebor, stated that the education and training programmes of ANAN meet internationally accepted accountancy standards. He also said ANAN is a member of the International Federation of Accountants (IFAC), Board Member of Pan African Federation of Accountants (PAFA) and the second-largest Professional Accountancy Organization in PAFA. He added that ANAN is recognised as the leading professional accountants’ organization in public sector accounting in Africa, adding that the body should be accorded its rightful place in the civil service.